{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312040415996d2f3320f24739","session_id":"5a4189c6-c669-4ea4-8c81-fee95bc26849","message":{"id":"20260312040415996d2f3320f24739","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_5518bb10642a4208b4050477","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# F-005: Pipeline Status Aggregation and Log Streaming — Tasks\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation (T-001 ~ T-009)\n\n- [ ] [T-001] [P] Create message-chunker utility — file: src/utils/message-chunker.js\n  - **Goal**: Implement message chunking utility that splits long content at line boundaries\n  - **Input**: Content string, chunk size limit\n  - **Output**: Array of chunks respecting Telegram message limits\n  - **Acceptance**: Chunks split at line boundaries, no UTF-8 character corruption, total chars per chunk ≤ 4000\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **US**: US-3\n\n- [ ] [T-002] [P] Create log-pager utility — file: src/utils/log-pager.js\n  - **Goal**: Implement paginated log reading with offset and line count support\n  - **Input**: Log file path, pagination params (lines, offset)\n  - **Output**: LogPage object with content, pagination metadata\n  - **Acceptance**: Supports offset/lines params, returns total lines, hasMore flag, nextOffset calculation\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **US**: US-2\n\n- [ ] [T-003] [P] Add unit tests for message-chunker — file: tests/utils/message-chunker.test.js\n  - **Goal**: Test message chunking with various inputs\n  - **Input**: Test cases: short message, long message, multi-byte UTF-8, single long line\n  - **Output**: Passing tests with >90% coverage\n  - **Acceptance**: All edge cases covered, UTF-8 boundary tests pass\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **US**: US-3\n\n- [ ] [T-004] [P] Add unit tests for log-pager — file: tests/utils/log-pager.test.js\n  - **Goal**: Test log pagination functionality\n  - **Input**: Test log files with various sizes\n  - **Output**: Passing tests with >90% coverage\n  - **Acceptance**: Offset handling, max lines enforcement, total count accuracy\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **US**: US-2\n\n- [ ] [T-005] Extend error codes for status aggregation — file: src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js\n  - **Goal**: Add new error codes for F-005 features\n  - **Input**: Existing error codes\n  - **Output**: Extended error codes including LOG_FILE_NOT_FOUND, STATE_PARSE_ERROR, NOTIFIER_SEND_FAILED\n  - **Acceptance**: New codes documented, exported correctly\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **US**: US-6\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Core Services (T-010 ~ T-099)\n\n- [ ] [T-010] Create pipeline-status-aggregator service — file: src/services/pipeline-status-aggregator.js\n  - **Goal**: Implement status aggregation from multiple state sources\n  - **Input**: Pipeline type (feature/bugfix)\n  - **Output**: AggregatedStatus object with phase, statistics, current target, errors\n  - **Acceptance**: Aggregates from state-manager, lock-manager, calculates statistics correctly\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **US**: US-1\n\n- [ ] [T-011] Implement statistics calculation — file: src/services/pipeline-status-aggregator.js\n  - **Goal**: Calculate completed/failed/skipped/pending counts from pipeline state\n  - **Input**: PipelineState, session history\n  - **Output**: StatisticsSummary object\n  - **Acceptance**: Accurate counts, success rate calculation\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **US**: US-1\n\n- [ ] [T-012] Implement error summary extraction — file: src/services/pipeline-status-aggregator.js\n  - **Goal**: Extract and format recent error information\n  - **Input**: Pipeline state, session logs\n  - **Output**: ErrorSummary with targetId, truncated message, timestamp\n  - **Acceptance**: Extracts last error, truncates to configured max length\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **US**: US-1, US-5\n\n- [ ] [T-013] Implement status message formatting — file: src/services/pipeline-status-aggregator.js\n  - **Goal**: Format aggregated status for Telegram display\n  - **Input**: AggregatedStatus object\n  - **Output**: Formatted string with emoji icons, clear structure\n  - **Acceptance**: Clear readable format, includes all AC-1.1~1.4 fields\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **US**: US-1\n\n- [ ] [T-014] Add unit tests for pipeline-status-aggregator — file: tests/services/pipeline-status-aggregator.test.js\n  - **Goal**: Test status aggregation logic\n  - **Input**: Mock state-manager, lock-manager responses\n  - **Output**: Passing tests with >90% coverage\n  - **Acceptance**: All aggregation scenarios covered, error handling tested\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **US**: US-1\n\n- [ ] [T-015] Create pipeline-notifier service skeleton — file: src/services/pipeline-notifier.js\n  - **Goal**: Create notifier service with Telegram bot integration\n  - **Input**: Bot instance, chat ID, config\n  - **Output**: Notifier instance with startHeartbeat, stopHeartbeat, notify* methods\n  - **Acceptance**: Service created, methods defined, config loaded\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **US**: US-4, US-5\n\n- [ ] [T-016] Implement heartbeat mechanism — file: src/services/pipeline-notifier.js\n  - **Goal**: Implement periodic status push\n  - **Input**: Heartbeat interval config\n  - **Output**: Heartbeat messages sent at configured interval\n  - **Acceptance**: Configurable interval, async non-blocking, proper cleanup on stop\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **US**: US-4\n\n- [ ] [T-017] Implement error auto-push — file: src/services/pipeline-notifier.js\n  - **Goal**: Push error summaries when targets fail\n  - **Input**: Error event with targetId, message\n  - **Output**: Telegram message with error summary and action button\n  - **Acceptance**: Auto-push on error, truncated message, inline button for full log\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **US**: US-5\n\n- [ ] [T-018] Implement message retry logic — file: src/services/pipeline-notifier.js\n  - **Goal**: Retry failed message sends with exponential backoff\n  - **Input**: Message text, options\n  - **Output**: Delivery confirmation or final failure\n  - **Acceptance**: