{"type":"user","uuid":"b710a1f9-60e0-462e-a1e5-7e02b697a0dc","session_id":"5a4189c6-c669-4ea4-8c81-fee95bc26849","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde8e74ad418daf4d254408ebdaa4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: bot\n   3→PATH: src/bot/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: Telegram bot handlers and command routing layer\n   5→\n   6→ENTRYPOINT:\n   7→- src/bot/telegram.js -> createTelegramBot() registers all commands and handlers\n   8→\n   9→KEY_FILES:\n  10→- src/bot/telegram.js - Main bot factory, command registration, text handler\n  11→- src/bot/commands/index.js - Router entry point, routeCommand()\n  12→- src/bot/commands/parser.js - Command text parser, parseCommand()\n  13→- src/bot/commands/registry.js - Command registration and lookup\n  14→- src/bot/commands/validator.js - Parameter validation\n  15→- src/bot/commands/formatter.js - Error message formatting\n  16→- src/bot/commands/help.js - Help text generation\n  17→- src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js - Individual command handlers\n  18→\n  19→SUBDIRS:\n  20→- src/bot/commands -> command routing and dispatch\n  21→- src/bot/commands/handlers -> individual command implementations\n  22→\n  23→INTERFACES:\n  24→- Telegram Commands:\n  25→  - /start - Bot startup greeting\n  26→  - /help - Dynamic help text\n  27→  - /reset - Clear chat session\n  28→  - /screenshot - Capture desktop screenshot\n  29→  - /exec <cmd> - Execute system command\n  30→  - /pipeline [action] [target] [--type=] - Pipeline management (alias: /p)\n  31→  - /bugfix <target> - Start bugfix pipeline (alias: /b)\n  32→  - /planner [action] [target] - Planner pipeline management\n  33→  - /status - Show pipeline status (alias: /s)\n  34→  - /logs [target] - View pipeline logs (alias: /l)\n  35→  - /stop [target] - Stop pipeline\n  36→  - /plan [action] [type] [version] - Plan file management (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n  37→\n  38→TRAPS:\n  39→- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()\n  40→- Large logs (>=4000 chars) sent as files\n  41→- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase\n  42→- Registry stores normalized command names\n  43→- F002-CRIT-001: Parser treats first non-option token as subcommand; validator must check if command has no subcommands and use parsed.subcommand as first positional param\n  44→\n  45→DECISIONS:\n  46→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-bot-commands | Add command routing layer with parser, registry, validator for pipeline commands\n  47→- 2026-03-12 | F-002-alias-mapping | Support command aliases /p, /b, /s, /l\n  48→- 2026-03-12 | F002-CRIT-001 | Fix positional args: validator uses parsed.subcommand as first positional when command has no subcommands\n  49→- 2026-03-12 | F-003-plan-command | Add /plan command with status/versions/use/rollback/validate subcommands for plan file management\n  50→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"019cde86ad9a0ae1a9c5cf86c76a0ac0","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:20:04.879Z","_requestId":"8c83b89fde8941858aa97e5b6b7114a4"}
