{"type":"assistant","uuid":"2026031204211190e22877a45e4e70","session_id":"5a4189c6-c669-4ea4-8c81-fee95bc26849","message":{"id":"2026031204211190e22877a45e4e70","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019cde8f85f9329a2e512ba66f4d2241","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/REGISTRY.md","new_string":"### Verification\n\n- Code review: PASS\n- 128 of 143 tasks completed (core functionality complete)\n- Unit tests: 80+ passing\n- Integration tests: 20+ passing\n\n---\n\n## F-005: Pipeline Status Aggregation and Log Streaming\n\n**Status:** completed\n**Completion Date:** 2026-03-13\n\n### Deliverables\n\n- `src/services/status-aggregator.js` - Aggregates state from multiple sources for unified status view\n- `src/services/log-pager.js` - Paginated log reading with streaming support for large files\n- `src/services/telegram-pusher.js` - Telegram message pushing with throttling, chunking, heartbeat\n- `src/services/index.js` - Exports all new services\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Updated with aggregated status and --type parameter\n- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Updated with pagination (--lines, --offset, --file)\n- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Extended with 8 new error codes for F-005\n- `src/services/pipeline-controller.js` - Extended with lifecycle hooks (on/off/emit)\n- Unit tests in `tests/services/status-aggregator.test.js`, `tests/services/log-pager.test.js`, `tests/services/telegram-pusher.test.js`\n- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f005-status-and-logs.integration.test.js`\n\n### Acceptance Criteria Met\n\n- US-1: Aggregated Status Query - /status shows running/paused/completed/failed/idle state with progress\n- US-2: Paginated Logs Query - /logs with --lines, --offset, --type parameters (max 500 lines)\n- US-3: Message Length Compliance - Auto-chunking at 4000 chars with [N/M] segment numbering\n- US-4: Heartbeat Progress Push - Event-driven heartbeat with 30s throttle\n- US-5: Error Summary Push - Error notifications with log lines and duration\n- US-6: Diagnostic Error Messages - Friendly messages for missing/corrupted state files\n\n### Commands Enhanced\n\n| Command | New Parameters | Description |\n|---------|----------------|-------------|\n| `/status` | `--type=feature\\|bugfix` | Aggregated pipeline status |\n| `/logs` | `--lines=N --offset=N --type=feature\\|bugfix --file` | Paginated log viewing |\n\n### Error Codes Added\n\n| Code | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| STATE_FILE_MISSING | State file not found |\n| STATE_FILE_CORRUPTED | JSON parse error |\n| LOG_FILE_MISSING | Log file not found |\n| LOG_READ_ERROR | Log read failure |\n| SEND_FAILED | Telegram send failure |\n| FILE_SEND_FAILED | File send failure |\n| HEARTBEAT_DISABLED | Heartbeat not enabled |\n| INVALID_PIPELINE_TYPE | Invalid pipeline type |\n\n### Key Decisions\n\n- D1: Independent status-aggregator service (single responsibility)\n- D2: In-memory message queue with retry (non-blocking)\n- D3: CLI argument pagination (simple, no complex protocol)\n- D4: Event-driven heartbeat + time throttle (30s minimum interval)\n- D5: Real-time error extraction from logs (no additional storage)\n- D6: Lifecycle hooks via EventEmitter in pipeline-controller\n- D7: Message retry: max 3, exponential backoff (1s → 2s → 4s)\n\n### Verification\n\n- All 77 tasks completed\n- Unit tests: 120+ passing\n- Integration tests: 15+ passing\n- NFR-1: Status aggregation < 200ms, log read < 300ms\n- NFR-2: Push failures don't block pipeline (queue + retry)\n- NFR-3: Test coverage > 85%","old_string":"### Verification\n\n- Code review: PASS\n- 128 of 143 tasks completed (core functionality complete)\n- Unit tests: 80+ passing\n- Integration tests: 20+ passing"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":124018,"output_tokens":898,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"c