{"type":"user","uuid":"28658902-e48a-42c2-ae74-156dcb86df4c","session_id":"5a4189c6-c669-4ea4-8c81-fee95bc26849","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde903ecc52ba80adf183cd8d5a9f","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me generate the final code review report:\n\n---\n\n# 📋 F-005 Code Review Report\n\n## Summary\n\n**Feature**: F-005 - Pipeline Status Aggregation and Log Streaming  \n**Review Date**: 2026-03-14  \n**Reviewer**: Reviewer Agent  \n**Verdict**: **PASS_WITH_WARNINGS**\n\n---\n\n## 1. Spec Compliance Analysis\n\n### US-1: Aggregated Status Query ✅\n\n| AC | Requirement | Status | Notes |\n|----|-------------|--------|-------|\n| AC-1.1 | Return pipeline stage (running/paused/completed/failed/idle) | ✅ PASS | `determinePipelineStage()` correctly identifies all stages |\n| AC-1.2 | Display feature statistics | ✅ PASS | `calculateProgress()` returns total/completed/failed/inProgress |\n| AC-1.3 | Display current feature ID and start time | ✅ PASS | `current` object includes featureId, startedAt, duration |\n| AC-1.4 | Display last run result summary | ✅ PASS | `lastResult` object populated when stage is idle |\n| AC-1.5 | Support `--type` parameter | ✅ PASS | Handler accepts `params.type` with 'feature'/'bugfix' |\n\n### US-2: Paginated Logs Query ✅\n\n| AC | Requirement | Status | Notes |\n|----|-------------|--------|-------|\n| AC-2.1 | Default 50 lines | ✅ PASS | `DEFAULT_LINES = 50` |\n| AC-2.2 | `--lines=N` max 500 | ✅ PASS | `MAX_LINES = 500` enforced |\n| AC-2.3 | `--offset=N` pagination | ✅ PASS | Offset parameter implemented |\n| AC-2.4 | `--type` pipeline type | ✅ PASS | Both feature/bugfix supported |\n| AC-2.5 | Friendly message for missing logs | ✅ PASS | Returns `📭 暂无日志...` message |\n\n### US-3: Message Length Compliance ✅\n\n| AC | Requirement | Status | Notes |\n|----|-------------|--------|-------|\n| AC-3.1 | Auto-segment > 4000 chars | ✅ PASS | `splitMessage()` handles correctly |\n| AC-3.2 | Segment numbering `[N/M]` | ✅ PASS | Added in `sendMessageChunked()` |\n| AC-3.3 | Segment interval ≥ 500ms | ✅ PASS | `DEFAULT_SEGMENT_INTERVAL = 500` |\n| AC-3.4 | `--file` option | ✅ PASS | `shouldSendAsFile()` and `sendFile()` implemented |\n\n### US-4: Heartbeat Progress Push ✅\n\n| AC | Requirement | Status | Notes |\n|----|-------------|--------|-------|\n| AC-4.1 | Startup notification with runId/targets | ✅ PASS | `pushStartupNotification()` implemented |\n| AC-4.2 | Progress check every N features | ✅ PASS | `heartbeatFeatureCount` configurable |\n| AC-4.3 | Progress includes completed/total/rate | ✅ PASS | `onFeatureCompleted()` includes stats |\n| AC-4.4 | Throttle ≥ 30s between pushes | ✅ PASS | `DEFAULT_THROTTLE_INTERVAL = 30000` |\n| AC-4.5 | Push to configured chatId | ✅ PASS | `targetChatId` parameter |\n\n### US-5: Error Summary Push ✅\n\n| AC | Requirement | Status | Notes |\n|----|-------------|--------|-------|\n| AC-5.1 | Push error summary on failure | ✅ PASS | `pushErrorSummary()` sends notification |\n| AC-5.2 | Display last N error lines | ✅ PASS | `errorLinesCount` configurable (default 10) |\n| AC-5.3 | Display execution time | ✅ PASS | Duration included in message |\n| AC-5.4 | Silent mode for expected failures | ✅ PASS | `silentMode` config + `isExpected` flag |\n\n### US-6: Diagnostic Error Messages ✅\n\n| AC | Requirement | Status | Notes |\n|----|-------------|--------|-------|\n| AC-6.1 | Missing state file message | ✅ PASS | Returns idle stage gracefully |\n| AC-6.2 | Missing log file message | ✅ PASS | Friendly message returned |\n| AC-6.3 | JSON parse error with file path | ✅ PASS | `readJsonFileSafe()` catches errors |\n| AC-6.4 | Diagnostic suggestions | ✅ PASS | Messages include hints |\n\n**Spec Compliance Score: 24/24 (100%)**\n\n---\n\n## 2. Plan Compliance Analysis\n\n### Interface Design Compliance\n\n| Component | Plan Interface | Implementation | Status |\n|-----------|----------------|----------------|--------|\n| status-aggregator | `aggregateStatus(type)` | ✅ Matches | Line 189 |\n| status-aggregator | `formatStatusForTelegram(status)` | ✅ Matches | Line 252 |\n| status-aggregator | `calculateProgress(state)` | ✅ Matches | Line 133 |\n| status-aggregator | `getErrorSummary(lastResult)` | ✅ Matches | Line 167 |\n| log-pager | `readLogPage(type, options)` | ✅ Matches | Line 129 |\n| log-pager | `extractErrorLines(logs, count)` | ✅ Matches | Line 225 |\n| log-pager | `shouldSendAsFile(logs, threshold)` | ✅ Matches | Line 246 |\n| log-pager | `formatLogsForTelegram(logs, metadata)` | ✅ Matches | Line 278 |\n| telegram-pusher | `sendMessageChunked(chatId, text)` | ✅ Matches | Line 111 |\n| telegram-pusher | `startHeartbeat(type, aggregator)` | ✅ Matches | Line 216 |\n| telegram-pusher | `stopHeartbeat(type)` | ✅ Matches | Line 247 |\n| telegram-pusher | `pushErrorSummary(type, featureId, error)` | ✅ Matches | Line 284 |\n\n**Plan Compliance Score: 12/12 (100%)**\n\n---\n\n## 3. Code Quality Analysis\n\n### Strengths\n- ✅ Factory pattern consistently used\n- ✅ Clear separation of concerns (aggregator, pager, pusher)\n- ✅ Comprehensive JSDoc comments\n- ✅ Proper async/await usage\n- ✅ Error handling with graceful degradation\n\n### Findings\n\n| ID | Severity | File | Line | Description |\n|----|----------|------|------|-------------|\n| CQ-01 | LOW | status-aggregator.js | 39-46 | `readJsonFileSafe` catches all errors silently - could log for debugging |\n| CQ-02 | MEDIUM | log-pager.js | 66-118 | `streamReadLastLines` reads file twice - could optimize with single pass |\n| CQ-03 | LOW | telegram-pusher.js | 41 | Multiple config sources could lead to confusion |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Security Analysis\n\n### Findings\n\n| ID | Severity | File | Line | Description | Recommendation |\n|----|----------|------|------|-------------|----------------|\n| SEC-01 | LOW | status-aggregator.js | 41 | No path validation on file reads | Consider validating paths are within expected directories |\n| SEC-02 | INFO | telegram-pusher.js | 124 | `parse_mode: 'Markdown'` could allow injection if user input included | Ensure user-controlled data is escaped |\n\n**No CRITICAL or HIGH security findings.**\n\n---\n\n## 5. Consistency Analysis\n\n### Pattern Compliance\n\n| Pattern | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| Factory functions | ✅ PASS | All modules use `create*()` factory pattern |\n| Error codes | ✅ PASS | Uses `INFRA_ERROR_CODES` from error-codes.js |\n| Config loading | ✅ PASS | Uses `loadPipelineInfraConfig()` |\n| State paths | ✅ PASS | Uses `getStatePaths()` from path-policy.js |\n\n### TRAPS Adherence\n\n| TRAP | Status | Notes |\n|------|--------|-------|\n| chat-queue serialization | N/A | Not applicable to F-005 |\n| script-runner delegation | ✅ PASS | Pipeline-controller properly delegates |\n| lock-manager usage | ✅ PASS | Pipeline-controller uses lock-manager |\n| runSingle no lock | ✅ PASS | Line 371 comment confirms D5 decision |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Coverage Analysis\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Module | Test File | Tests | Coverage |\n|--------|-----------|-------|----------|\n| status-aggregator.js | status-aggregator.test.js | 15 | High |\n| log-pager.js | log-pager.test.js | 17 | High |\n| telegram-pusher.js | telegram-pusher.test.js | 19 | High |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| User Story | Tests | Status |\n|------------|-------|--------|\n| US-1 | 4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-2 | 4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-3 | 4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-4 | 5 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-5 | 4 | ✅ PASS |\n| US-6 | 4 | ✅ PASS |\n| Edge Cases | 6 | ✅ PASS |\n\n**Estimated Coverage: >85% (meets NFR-3)**\n\n---\n\n## 7. NFR Compliance\n\n| NFR | Requirement | Status | Notes |\n|-----|-------------|--------|-------|\n| NFR-1 | Status aggregation < 200ms | ✅ PASS | Simple file reads, no heavy computation |\n| NFR-1 | Log read (100 lines) < 300ms | ✅ PASS | Efficient file reading |\n| NFR-1 | Message sending non-blocking | ✅ PASS | Async queue with fire-and-forget |\n| NFR-2 | Push failure non-blocking | ✅ PAS